TIME_COMPLEXITY : O(n)
SPACE_COMPLEXITY : O(1)
APPROACH : The optimal approach interleaves copied nodes within the original list by inserting each copy right after its original node. Then, random pointers are assigned using temp.next.random = temp.random.next. Finally, the combined list is split to restore the original list and extract the copied list. This method runs in O(n) time and uses O(1) space.